column5: I must be dreaming or something cause I can't believe, I wasn't able to catch a fish this season   Been out 6 times this hardwater season and not a sniff for my efforts   I don't know how to feel about it but one thing's for sure... end of April, and it all start again    Made this little video and those that can't stand my choice of music, please mute the sound    otherwise... crank her up and enjoy  TJunkiehttp://s732.photobucket.com/user/leechman1/media/Hard%20Water%202013/TroutJunkies2013HardwaterSeason_zps165155ad.mp4.html
Common up here for a few days, still 4 feet + of ice and some nice lakers,    I wasn't able to open up your link
I hear you about the ice... lots left down here... 24"+ but the fishes are on vacation   and not interested in any offerings I / we present   The end for me until opener   Thanks B
pinch   shame about the hard water for you this year J - but its not long till soft water opener now. Myabe they're just wating to give you a limit-full spring?
Youre not alone unfortunately. This winter was my first attempt at ice fishing, been out 5-6 times to 3 different bodies of water and nothing! Cant wait for summer!

What a difference a few decades can make. Here I sit on a Saturday night, watching for the Easter Bunny, watching my dear wife watching TV, watching the cat watch me watching my wife watching TV, and me watching a video watching a guy not catch fish. Oh my. I miss the discos, and my fishing. If the stores were open tomorrow I'd be in line to buy a new boat battery. I need some professional help, soon, and a battery.

Hey Rick, yeah, I feel terrible now   but come end of April and it's another season starting   maybe the fishing god will be on my side   but will give it my best   Nice shot Paul   but wish it was of a speck on ice   Guess we have something in common... a perfect fishing record   A few  decades ago?  Wish it was 2008.... a most productive year fishing wise for me
